Afropop singing sensation, Yemi Alade has lamented over the inconvenience she endures when she has to put on a jean. The “Johnny” singer in an Instagram post, groaned about the inconvenience her massive backside puts her through every time she has to wear a jean. The 33-year-old said she has to jump in order to wear her jeans.   MI Abaga seeks financial support for ailing Eedris Abdul…     Moving abroad changed my life – Wakawaka Doctor     My dad had an ex-wife, says Bovi’s daughter   According to Alade, anyone who doesn’t experience similar struggle with their jeans cannot relate with her pain. “If you don’t jump, to put jeans on, baby you can’t feel my pain,” she wrote.